{{t+|uk|на́ція|f}}, {{t+|uk|наро́д|m}}\n* Urdu: {{t+|ur|قَوم|f}}\n* Uyghur: {{t|ug|مىللەت}}\n* Uzbek: {{t+|uz|millat}}, {{t+|uz|ulus}}\n* Vietnamese: {{t+|vi|dân tộc}}, {{t+|vi|quốc dân}}\n* Welsh: {{t+|cy|cenedl|f}}\n* Yiddish: {{t|yi|פֿאָלק|n}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|sovereign state}}\n* Afrikaans: {{t+|af|nasie}}, {{t+|af|staat}}\n* Albanian: {{t+|sq|shtet|m}}\n* Amharic: {{t|am|መንግሥት}}, {{t|am|ሃገር|f}}\n* Arabic: {{t+|ar|دَوْلَة|f}}, {{t+|ar|وَطَن|m}}\n* Armenian: {{t+|hy|պետություն}}, {{t+|hy|երկիր}}\n* Azerbaijani: {{t+|az|dövlət}}\n* Bashkir: {{t|ba|ил}}, {{t|ba|дәүләт}}, {{t|ba|дәүләт}}\n* Belarusian: {{t+|be|дзяржа́ва|f}}, {{t+|be|на́цыя|f}}\n* Bengali: {{t+|bn|রাষ্ট্র}}, {{t+|bn|জাতি}}\n* Bikol:\n*: Central Bikol: {{t|bcl|nasyon}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|държа́ва|f}}\n* Burmese: {{t+|my|နိုင်ငံ}}\n* Catalan: {{t+|ca|estat|m}}\n* Cebuano: {{t|ceb|nasod}}\n* Chavacano: {{t|cbk|nacion}}\n* Chichewa: {{t|ny|dziko}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Cantonese: {{t|yue|國家}}\n*: Dungan: {{t|dng|гуйҗя}}\n*: Eastern Min: {{t|cdo|國家}}\n*: Hakka: {{t|hak|國家|tr=koet-kâ}}\n*: Hokkien: {{t+|nan-hbl|國家|tr=kok-ka}}\n*: Mandarin: {{t+|cmn|國家}}\n*: Northern Min: {{t|mnp|國家}}\n*: Wu: {{t|wuu|國家}}\n* Crimean Tatar: {{t|crh|devlet}}\n* Czech: {{t+|cs|stát|m}}\n* Danish: {{t|da|stat|c}}\n* Dutch: {{t+|nl|natie|f}}, {{t+|nl|staat|m}}\n* Estonian: {{t+|et|riik}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|kansakunta}}, {{t+|fi|valtio}}, {{t+|fi|kansa}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|état|m}}, {{t+|fr|État|m}}, {{t+|fr|Etat|m}}\n* Galician: {{t+|gl|estado|m}}\n* Georgian: {{t+|ka|სახელმწიფო}}\n* German: {{t+|de|Staat|m}}\n* Greek: {{t+|el|κράτος|n}}, {{t+|el|καθεστώς|n}}\n* Hebrew: {{t+|he|מְדִינָה|f|tr=mediná|alt=מדינה \\ מְדִינָה}}, {{t+|he|אֻמָּה|f|tr=ummá}}\n* Hiligaynon: {{t|hil|pungsud}}, {{t|hil|nasyon}}\n* Hindi: {{t+|hi|राज्य|m}}, {{t+|hi|राष्ट्र|m}}, {{t+|hi|जाति|f}}\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|ország}}, {{t+|hu|állam}}\n* Icelandic: {{t+|is|ríki|n}}\n* Ilocano: {{t|ilo|nasion}}\n* Indonesian: {{t+|id|negara}}\n* Irish: {{t|ga|stát|m}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|stato|m}}, {{t+|it|nazione|f}}\n* Japanese: {{t+|ja|国家|tr=こっか, kokka}}\n* Karen:\n*: Pa'o Karen: {{t+|blk|ခမ်းထီ}}\n* Kazakh: {{t+|kk|мемлекет}}\n* Khmer: {{t+|km|រដ្ឋ}}, {{t+|km|ប្រទេស}}\n* Korean: {{t+|ko|국가(國家)}}\n* Kyrgyz: {{t+|ky|мамлекет}}\n* Lao: {{t+|lo|ລັດ}}, {{t+|lo|ຊາດ}}, {{t|lo|ປະເທດ}}\n* Latin: {{t+|la|natio|f}}\n* Latvian: {{t+|lv|valsts|f}}\n* Lithuanian: {{t+|lt|valstybė|f}}\n* Low German:\n*: German Low German: {{t+|nds-de|Staat|m}}, {{t+|nds-de|Stoot|m}}\n* Macedonian: {{t|mk|држава|f}}\n* Malay: {{t|ms|bangsa}}, {{t+|ms|negara}}\n* Manchu: {{t|mnc|ᡤᡠᡵᡠᠨ}}, {{t|mnc|ᡤᡠᡵᡠᠨ ᠪᠣᠣ}}\n* Marathi: {{t|mr|राष्ट्र|n}}\n* Mongolian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{t|mn|улс гурэн}}, {{t+|mn|улс}}\n* Norwegian:\n*: Bokmål: {{t+|nb|stat|m}}\n*: Nynorsk: {{t|nn|stat|m}}\n* Old Church Slavonic:\n*: Cyrillic: {{t|cu|землꙗ|f}}, {{t|cu|страна|f}}\n* Old East Slavic: {{t|orv|землꙗ|f}}, {{t|orv|краина|f}}\n* Old English: {{t|ang|þēod|f}}\n* Oromo: {{t|om|biyya}}\n* Pashto: {{t+|ps|دولت|m|tr=dawlát}}\n* Persian:\n*: Dari: {{t|prs|دَوْلَت|tr=dawlat}}\n*: Iranian Persian: {{t+|fa|دُوْلَت|tr=dowlat}}\n* Plautdietsch: {{t+|pdt|Launt|n}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|stan|m}}, {{t+|pl|nacja|f}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|estado|m}}\n* Romanian: {{t+|ro|stat|n}}\n* Romansh: {{t|rm|stadi|m}}, {{t|rm|naziun|f}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|госуда́рство|n}}, {{t+|ru|держа́ва|f}}\n* Serbo-Croatian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{t|sh|др̀жава|f}}\n*: Latin: {{t+|sh|dr̀žava|f}}\n* Sinhalese: {{t|si|රාජ්‍යය}}, {{t|si|ජාතිය}}\n* Slovak: {{t+|sk|štát|m}}\n* Slovene: {{t+|sl|država|f}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|estado|m}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|stat|c}}\n* Tagalog: {{t+|tl|bansa}}, {{t|tl|nasyon}}\n* Tajik: {{t+|tg|давлат}}\n* Tatar: {{t+|tt|дәүләт}}\n* Thai: {{t+|th|รัฐ}}, {{t+|th|ชาติ}}, {{t+|th|ประเทศ}}\n* Tibetan: {{t|bo|རྒྱལ་ཁབ}}\n* Turkish: {{t+|tr|devlet}}\n*: Ottoman Turkish: {{t|ota|ایل|tr=il}}\n* Turkmen: {{t|tk|döwlet}}\n* Ugaritic: {{t|uga|𐎈𐎆𐎚}}\n* Ukrainian: {{t+|uk|держа́ва|f}}, {{t+|uk|на́ція|f}}\n* Urdu: {{t|ur|رِیاسَت|f}}\n* Uyghur: {{t|ug|دۆلەت}}\n* Uzbek: {{t+|uz|davlat}}\n* Vietnamese: {{t+|vi|nhà nước}}, {{t+|vi|quốc gia}}\n* Yiddish: {{t|yi|מדינה|f|tr=medine}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|association of students}}\n* Catalan: {{t+|ca|sindicat|m}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|osakunta}}\n* Galician: {{t+|gl|nación|m}}\n* German: {{t+|de|Nation|f}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|nation|f}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|землячество|n}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|sindicato|m}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|nation|c}}, {{t|sv|studentnation|c}}\n* Uyghur: {{t|ug|ئۇيۇشما}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n=====See also=====\n{{col3|en|country|culture|homeland|ethnicity|people|race|society|state}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\nShort for {{m|en|damnation}} or {{m|en|tarnation}}.\n\n====Alternative forms====\n* {{alt|en|'nation}}\n\n====Noun====\n{{en-noun|?}}\n\n# {{lb|en|rare}} [[damnation|Damnation]].\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1875|title=Lippincott's Magazine of Popular Literature and Science|page=611\n|text=... what the '''nation's''' the matter of that boy now ? If he's got them highsterics ag'in , I'll blister him from the crown of his head to the soles of his feet , sure as he's a - livin ' . \" The doctor took up his hat and started out to meet{{nb...}}}}\n#* '''1896''', Hardy, ''Laodicean'', page 487, quoted in the ''EDD'':\n#*: O '''nation!'''.. if I were a man, {{...}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1897|author=George Bartram|title=People of Clopton|page=193\n|passage=What the '''nation's''' the matter now?}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|date=2025-03-02|author=Warren H. Miller|title=Red Mesa : A tale of the southwest|publisher=Good Press\n|text=\"What the '''nation's''' the matter with our John?\" he broke off suddenly as his eyes fell on the occupant of the cot.}}\n\n====Adverb====\n{{en-adv|?}}\n\n# {{lb|en|rare|dialectal}}<!--US and UK--> [[extremely|Extremely]], [[very]].\n#* {{RQ:Twain Huckleberry Finn|chapter=XIX|page=186|passage=“Looky here, Bilgewater,” he says, “I’m '''nation''' sorry for you, but you ain’t the only person that’s had troubles like that.”}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1856|author=Mary Botham Howitt|title=My uncle the clockmaker|page=10\n|text=\"Beleddy, Mester, yo're a dab hand at axing questions, at ony rate! One has to look back a ''''nation''' long way into one's books to find what yo I axen after.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1896|author=English Dialect Society|title=Publications|page=71\n|text=But no sense ov a place, some think, Is this here hill so high, - 'Cos there, full oft, 'tis '''nation''' coad, But that don't argufy. }}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1899|author=Thomas Hardy|title=The trumpet major|page=122\n|text='... they seem ''''nation''' fond of one another.' 'He haven't knowed her such a very long time,' said Job Mitchell dubiously. }}\n\n====Adjective====\n{{en-adj|?}}\n\n# {{lb|en|rare|dialectal}}<!--US and UK--> {{n-g|An intensifier;}} [[extreme]], [[great]].\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1839|author=Grace Darling|title=Grace Darling, or the Heroine of the Fern Islands. A tale founded on recent facts. [With plates.]|page=4\n|text=... a '''nation''' deal o' trouble to captivate him.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1840|title=Sporting Magazine|page=227\n|text=... a '''nation''' lot of hunters assembled, for it war known there war plenty of game ...}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1885|author=John Hankins Wallace|title=Wallace's Monthly: An Illustrated Magazine Devoted to Domesticated Animal Nature|page=431\n|text=... a '''nation''' sight o' buzzin' an', ez Mr. Mayfield says, }}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1892|author=Isabella Banks|author2=Mrs. George Linnaeus Banks|title=Glory|page=59\n|text=I might not have been in such a '''nation''' hurry to jump from my cart to keep him from being pitched on the stones!}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1968|title=Graham's Illustrated Magazine of Literature, Romance, Art, and Fashion\n|text=... a '''nation''' sight o' good.}}\n\n===References===\n* {{cite-web|title=Notable and Quotable|work=Merriam Webster Online Newsletter|date=November 2005|url=http://www.word.com/unabridged/archives/2005/11/notable_and_quo_4.html|accessdate=December 23, 2005|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060314201338/http://www.word.com/unabridged/archives/2005/11/notable_and_quo_4.html|archivedate=14 March 2006}}.\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|en|a=ainnot|Tonian|anoint}}\n\n{{c|en|Collectives|Polities}}\n\n==Danish==\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{der|da|la|nātiō||birth, people}}, derived from the verb {{m|la|nāscor||to be born}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|da|[naˈɕoˀn]}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{da-noun|en|er}}\n\n# a {{l|en|nation}}, a people with a common identity, united in history, culture or language\n# a {{l|en|nation}}, a country that is a politically independent unity\n\n====Declension====\n{{da-decl|en|er}}\n\n===References===\n* {{R:DDO}}\n\n==French==\n{{wp|fr:}}\n\n===Etymology===\n{{ety|fr|:inh|frm:nation}}\n{{inh+|fr|frm|nation}}, from {{inh|fr|fro|nacion}}, borrowed from {{bor|fr|la|natio|nātiōnem}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{fr-IPA}}\n* {{audio|fr|Fr-nation.ogg}}\n* {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-Poslovitch-nation.wav|a=<<France>> (<<Vosges>>)}}\n* {{rhymes|fr|ɔ̃|s=2}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{fr-noun|f}}\n\n# {{l|en|nation}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col3|fr\n|national\n|Nations Unies\n|Organisation des Nations Unies\n|Six Nations\n|Société des Nations}}\n\n====Descendants====\n* {{desc|ht|nasyon}}\n* {{desc|pms|nassion|bor=1}}\n\n===References===\n* {{R:fr:TLFi}}\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{l|fr|tonnai}}\n\n==Middle English==\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|enm|noun|altform=1}}\n\n# {{tlb|enm|Parliamentary Rolls}} {{alt form|enm|nacioun}}\n\n{{cat|enm|Late Middle English}}\n\n==Middle French==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{ety|frm|:inh|fro:nacion}}\nFrom {{inh|frm|fro|nacion}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{frm-noun|f}}\n\n# {{l|en|nation}}\n\n====Descendants====\n* {{desctree|fr|nation}}\n\n==Swedish==\n{{wp|sv:}}\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|sv|/natˈɧuːn/}}\n* {{audio|sv|Sv-nation.ogg}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{sv-noun|c}}\n\n# {{l|en|nation}}, [[country]], [[state]]\n# {{l|en|nation}}, [[people]]\n#: {{ux|sv|tala till '''nationen'''|address the '''nation'''}}\n# a [[union]] or [[fraternity]] of [[student]]s from the same [[province]]\n\n====Declension====\n{{sv-infl-noun-c-er}}\n\n====Related terms====\n{{col|sv\n|Förenta nationerna\n|national-\n|nationaldag\n|nationalism\n|nationalist\n|nationalitet\n|nationell\n|Nationernas förbund\n|nationshus\n|nationsliv\n|studentnation\n}}\n\n===References===\n* {{R:svenska.se|so}}\n* {{R:svenska.se|saol}}\n* {{R:svenska.se|saol}}"}}